    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">HESCO Reference Number — Where is it on Your Bill?</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">The HESCO reference number is a 14-digit number on the top-right section of your electricity bill. It is the key to checking your HESCO bill online and making payments through any bank or mobile wallet.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Where is the reference number on HESCO bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The HESCO reference number is on the top-right of your bill, labeled Ref. No. It is a 14-digit number printed in bold above the barcode. HESCO covers Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Tharparkar, Badin, Sanghar, and surrounding Sindh districts.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is HESCO reference number format?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The HESCO reference number is always 14 digits — no letters or dashes. It is the same every month unless WAPDA reassigns your meter. Your 10-digit Customer ID never changes.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">HESCO helpline for reference number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Call HESCO helpline 022-9200301 or dial 118 from any network. Provide your name, address, and CNIC. The helpline can give you your HESCO reference number immediately.</div></details>
